{
  "texts": [
    "For each input, the execution time is measured 10 times, resulting in (10 × 1000) data points per study.",
    "The standard deviation (std) of the 10 measurements is calculated for each input, yielding 1000 std values.",
    "In the CD case study, the maximum std among these 1000 std values was remarkably low at 2680.72 ns.",
    "This value is negligible given the execution times ranging from 50 to 200 microseconds.",
    "Similarly, in the 6-DOF case study, where execution times are around 10 milliseconds, the maximum std observed was about 40 microseconds, again demonstrating minimal variability."
  ]
}